      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "\"Finding peace can mean different things to different people. For some, it might be about letting go of the struggle and finding a way to move forward without the burden of what you're going through. It's important to remember that you're not alone, and there are people who care about you and want to help. Sometimes, taking a step back and focusing on self-care can bring a sense of calm and clarity. But it's also okay to seek professional help if you're feeling overwhelmed. Finding peace is a personal journey, and it's okay to take your time to figure out what that means for you.\"",
      "source": "target",
